nted. Their experiences highlight the importance of the sense of belonging and being, connectedness, continuity and a coherent growth in identity formation. Their attachment to a particular locality and their commitment to perform the moral guide role as EIL teachers serve as the most powerful platform for all their other identities to be constructed, negotiated and reconstituted.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexGlobalization. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aLanguage and culture. 0aLanguage teachers. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aEFL teachers.  aEiL.  aEnglish as an International language.  aVietnam.  aidentity.  alanguage teacher identity.  anon-Western philosophies.1 aEdwards, Viv, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHa, Phan Le, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769050040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847690500423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847690500/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK